comments:
Created 1.4.1934 out of the parishes of Sulhamstead Bannister 
    and Wokefield. See also Table 2, note (h).
Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Sulhamstead.

Created 1.4.1934 out of the parishes of Sulhamstead Abbots and 
    Sulhamstead bannister Upper End. See also Table 2, note (h).

Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Sulhamstead 
    Bannister.
Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Sulhamstead.

Created 1894 out of the parish of Tilehurst. See also Table 2, 
    notes (d) and (h).

In 1894 the part in Berkshire became 
    part of the parish of Purley, so that thereafter Whitchurch was entirely in Oxfordshire. 
    See also Table 2, note (e).

That part which until 9.11.1911 formed parts of the parishes 
    of Theale and Tilehurst. See also Table 2, note (d).
